OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCulture secretary urges    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Freversal of Channel 4 sale 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Culture Secretary Michelle Donelan has 
OL,6, advised against the privatisation of   
OL,7, Channel 4 in a letter to the prime     
OL,8, minister that has leaked online.       
OL,10,FIn the letter, obtained by the News    
OL,11,FAgents podcast, Ms Donelan said there  
OL,12,Fwere "better ways to ensure Channel 4's
OL,13,Fsustainability" than privatisation.    
OL,15,FHer predecessor Nadine Dorries, who    
OL,16,Fplanned to sell the government-owned   
OL,17,Fchannel, criticised the reversal.      
OL,19,FBut Ms Donelan said "pursuing a sale at
OL,20,Fthis point is not the right decision". 
